<span id="freeTextContainer2369868234029952829">“ Zozie de l&apos;Alba has breezed into Vianne/ Yanne&apos;s life. What&apos;s she up to ? She who steals identities, is fun, has loads of magic. And Yanne (from Chocolat) why has she turned into such a wimp. Why is she trying to conform, be like &quot;the others&quot;, of course its because she wants a normal life for her daughters Anouk/Annie and Rosette (who is mute). Although Zozie&apos;s intentions are far from good, she does manage to get Yanne back into business, she manages to inject a lot of life into the Chocolat s</span>
  <span id="freeText2369868234029952829" style="display:none">“ Zozie de l'Alba has breezed into Vianne/ Yanne's life. What's she up to ? She who steals identities, is fun, has loads of magic. And Yanne (from Chocolat) why has she turned into such a wimp. Why is she trying to conform, be like "the others", of course its because she wants a normal life for her daughters Anouk/Annie and Rosette (who is mute). Although Zozie's intentions are far from good, she does manage to get Yanne back into business, she manages to inject a lot of life into the Chocolat shop which was just an ordinary shop before Zozie took over. Bad intentions Zozie...you tried to take away Anouk from her mother, but failed. Anouk stayed on with Yanne stronger than before, but why did she need Pantoufle and Rosette her Bam ? Chocolat had only good intentions but Lollipop Shoes shows that the world has evil in it too, even if it is the form of the very glamorous Zozie de l'Alba. ” </span>
